Heather Dunbar.

347
00:19:53,770 --> 00:19:55,760
我觉得她会是位很棒的法官
I think she'd be an excellent justice.

348
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:57,160
很高兴你同意选她
I'm glad you agree.

349
00:19:57,160 --> 00:20:00,760
只是没想到会选她  毕竟她...
Just an unlikely choice, given how vociferous she--

350
00:20:00,760 --> 00:20:02,580
在沃克调查中咄咄逼人  是的
With the Walker investigation, yes.

351
00:20:02,580 --> 00:20:05,100
但那只会增加我对她的尊重
But that only increases my estimation of her.

352
00:20:05,210 --> 00:20:07,020
她很有责任感
She has a great sense of duty.

353
00:20:07,140 --> 00:20:10,050
比我共事过的任何副检察长都有责任心
More than any Solicitor General I've ever worked with.

354
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:14,680
真希望我早能知道您找我来的原因
I wish I'd known the reason you invited me beforehand.

355
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,400
就可以免去这趟麻烦了
I could have saved you the trouble.

356
00:20:16,450 --> 00:20:17,300
为什么呢
Why?

357
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:19,790
我几个月前跟您聊过之后
After I talked to you a couple of months ago,

358
00:20:20,150 --> 00:20:22,090
露丝说您是给了我一份礼物
Ruth said you'd given me a gift.

359
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:25,380
如果我不当法官  会很痛苦
That I would be miserable if I weren't on the bench.

360
00:20:25,380 --> 00:20:28,850
她跟我儿子都谈了  他们也同意
She talked to my sons and they all agreed.

361
00:20:28,850 --> 00:20:30,740
只要我的健康还允许
As long as I'm well enough to serve the court,

362
00:20:30,740 --> 00:20:32,200
我就想继续做下去
that's where I want to be.

363
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,550
我们留意着点2016的走势
And we'll keep an eye on 2016.

364
00:20:35,550 --> 00:20:40,050
如果共和党看上去能赢  我就辞职
If it looks as though the Republicans will win, I'll step down.

365
00:20:40,050 --> 00:20:43,200
如果不会  我就留下  但不用着急
If not, I'll stay. But, there's no rush.

366
00:20:48,760 --> 00:20:50,630
我非得毁掉这个人吗
Must I destroy this man?

367
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:52,450
总统先生
Mr. President?

368
00:20:57,030 --> 00:20:59,950
不  我不想
No. I won't.

369
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:01,150
您说什么
Excuse me?

370
00:21:04,860 --> 00:21:07,480
我不能袖手旁观
I won't stand by

371
00:21:08,170 --> 00:21:10,590
看你做这个错误的决定
and watch you make this mistake.

372
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:14,400
我已经考虑好了
I've thought this through.

373
00:21:15,970 --> 00:21:17,520
我们不是朋友  罗伯特
We're not friends, Robert.

374
00:21:17,520 --> 00:21:20,080
我们没那么熟
We don't know each other that well.

375
00:21:20,140 --> 00:21:21,580
但我关心你
But I care about you.

376
00:21:22,090 --> 00:21:25,390
因为你在法院服务了超过20年
Because you served for more than 20 years on the bench.

377
00:21:25,390 --> 00:21:28,220
你裁定的判例存世会比你我都长久
You've established legal precedents that will outlive both of us.

378
00:21:28,220 --> 00:21:29,130
而且...
And...

379
00:21:29,130 --> 00:21:32,420
昨天的事你也许可以用人老糊涂解释过去
maybe you can explain away yesterday as a senior moment.

380
00:21:32,420 --> 00:21:35,620
但要是再出现你没法解释的其他状况呢
But what if another moment happens that you can't explain away?

381
00:21:35,620 --> 00:21:39,170
万一你患病的消息泄露出去了呢
What if somehow the news of your illness leaks?

382
00:21:39,190 --> 00:21:42,700
那你写下的每个判决都会受人怀疑
Then every decision you've written will be called into question.

383
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:43,900
都将受到质疑
They'll be challenged.

384
00:21:43,900 --> 00:21:47,400
你一生的成果瞬间就会化为乌有
And a life's work will be undone in a heartbeat.

385
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:50,420
您有什么其他心思吗
Do you have some ulterior motive here?

386
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:52,580
只是为你着想
Only your best interests.

387
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,430
那为什么要这么急
But why the urgency?

388
00:21:57,610 --> 00:21:59,160
我想保护你
I want to protect you.

389
00:22:00,530 --> 00:22:04,160
大法官  我在请求你  在恳求你
Justice, I'm asking you, I'm pleading with you.

390
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:08,650
别让事情脱离你的掌控
Don't let events get out of your control.

391
00:22:09,340 --> 00:22:10,720
你能重新考虑吗
Will you reconsider?

392
00:22:13,110 --> 00:22:15,480
谢谢您的关心  总统先生
I appreciate your concern, Mr. President.

393
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:19,940
我再跟露丝商量一下  给您答复
Let me speak again to Ruth and I'll get back to you.

394
00:22:20,750 --> 00:22:22,070
谢谢你  大法官
Thank you, Justice.

395
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:23,690
你这是禁言
It's a moratorium.

396
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:25,040
我们不那么叫
We're not calling it that.

397
00:22:25,040 --> 00:22:26,930
随你们叫什么  但没人开口
Call it whatever you want, nobody's talking.

398
00:22:27,190 --> 00:22:28,890
我们在避免发布错误信息
We're trying to prevent misinformation.

399
00:22:28,890 --> 00:22:30,810
我本想写《美就法》的报道
I'm supposed to write about AmWorks.

400
00:22:30,810 --> 00:22:31,880
但行政部门都
How can I do that  when no one

401
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,900
没人跟我说话我该怎么写
from the executive branch will speak to me?

402
00:22:33,900 --> 00:22:35,840
国会那边情况瞬息万变
This thing's shifting under our feet in Congress.

403
00:22:35,840 --> 00:22:38,420
等我写完早简报  已经成了昨日黄花
By the time I finish the morning brief, it's already outdated.

404
00:22:38,420 --> 00:22:41,080
我不是要求跟总统一对一对话  但...
I'm not asking for a one-on-one with the president, but...

405
00:22:41,330 --> 00:22:42,990
但劳工部长  财政部长
the Secretary of Labor, Treasury,

406
00:22:42,990 --> 00:22:44,340
他的哪个经济顾问都行
one of his economic advisors.

407
00:22:44,350 --> 00:22:45,870
给你特殊待遇吗
Give you special treatment?

408
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:49,040
我觉得你们下令禁言是因为你们要输
I think you issued the moratorium because you're losing the battle.

409
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:51,030
事关五千亿美金
It's 500 billion dollars.

410
00:22:51,150 --> 00:22:53,410
这是罗斯福新政以来最大的就业计划
This is the largest jobs program since the New Deal.

411
00:22:53,420 --> 00:22:56,350
当然是场激战  但那不代表我们失利
Of course it's a slugfest. That doesn't mean we're losing.

412
00:22:56,590 --> 00:22:58,740
那让我跟能确证那点的人谈谈
Then let me speak to someone who can confirm that.

413
00:22:58,990 --> 00:23:01,180
因为我从共和党人那里听到的
Because all I'm hearing from the Republicans is that

414
00:23:01,180 --> 00:23:02,790
都是《美就法》绝对不会通过
AmWorks will never see the light of day.

415
00:23:02,790 --> 00:23:04,140
我很同情你  艾拉
I sympathize with you, Ayla.

416
00:23:04,140 --> 00:23:06,090
我也希望能让你如愿
I wish I could give you what you want.

417
00:23:07,680 --> 00:23:08,720
总统要我们过去
The president needs us.

418
00:23:09,480 --> 00:23:10,550
我们迟点再聊
So we'll talk later.

419
00:23:12,190 --> 00:23:14,740
迈克尔·科里根  上周国宴时
Michael Corrigan, the activist who organized the protest

420
00:23:14,740 --> 00:23:16,230
组织抗议的激进分子
at the state dinner last month,

421
00:23:16,230 --> 00:23:18,810
三小时前在莫斯科被俄国警方逮捕
arrested by Russian police three hours ago in Moscow.

422
00:23:19,290 --> 00:23:20,570
视频已经疯传
The video is going viral.

423
00:23:21,210 --> 00:23:25,940
他是国内外知名的同性恋权利活动家
He's a high profile gay rights activist, nationally and abroad.

424
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:29,400
过去六周以来他一直在俄罗斯高调活动
And he's been very vocal in Russia over the last six weeks.

425
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:31,110
这是联调局关于他的档案  先生
Here's the bureau file on him, sir.

426
00:23:31,230 --> 00:23:32,920
我们跟克里姆林宫接触了吗
Have we been in touch with the Kremlin?

427
00:23:32,930 --> 00:23:35,380
杜兰特国务卿现在正在丹吉尔[摩洛哥城市]
Secretary Durant is in Tangier right now.

428
00:23:35,380 --> 00:23:38,300
我打电话知会了她  她也联系了布加耶夫
I briefed her by phone and she reached out to Bugayev.

429
00:23:38,300 --> 00:23:40,200
但他们还没有联系上
But they have not connected yet.

430
00:23:40,230 --> 00:23:42,720
格莱姆斯大使也在莫斯科上下疏通
Ambassador Grimes is making calls in Moscow,

431
00:23:42,720 --> 00:23:43,750
但目前没有进展
but nobody's engaging,

432
00:23:43,750 --> 00:23:46,710
只知道他们打算提出严重的指控
other than to say they plan on fully prosecuting him.

433
00:23:47,420 --> 00:23:49,190
大使  你认为这会不会是对你在联合国
Ambassador, do you think this could be in retaliation

434
00:23:49,190 --> 00:23:50,770
活动的报复行为
for what you're doing at the UN?

435
00:23:50,860 --> 00:23:51,920
有这个可能
It could be.

436
00:23:52,330 --> 00:23:55,100
俄罗斯人对这个决议案非常不满
The Russians are very upset about this resolution.

437
00:23:55,330 --> 00:23:57,310
我去莫里科夫那里探探口风
I'll see what I can find out from Moryakov.

438
00:23:58,120 --> 00:24:00,160
把新闻发布会推迟到明天
Let's hold off on the press conference until tomorrow.

439
00:24:00,160 --> 00:24:02,340
我希望能汇报些好消息  而不是两手空空
I'd like to deliver some good news instead of no news.

440
00:24:02,340 --> 00:24:03,170
同时
In the meantime,

441
00:24:03,220 --> 00:24:05,610
发一个声明  说我们正在接触莫斯科方面
put out a statement that we're in communication with Moscow.

442
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:07,460
我们正竭尽所能
And that we're doing everything we can

443
00:24:07,460 --> 00:24:09,480
把科里根先生营救回美国  谢谢各位
to get Mr. Corrigan back to the United States. Thank you all.

444
00:24:11,390 --> 00:24:12,670
我个人也讨厌这套法律
Personally, I hate the law.

445
00:24:12,670 --> 00:24:14,780
古板又恐同的玩意
It's medieval homophobic nonsense.

446
00:24:14,780 --> 00:24:15,930
但法律就是法律
But it's the law.

447
00:24:16,010 --> 00:24:17,210
我们刚刚谈过
I don't think it's coincidence

448
00:24:17,210 --> 00:24:19,530
科里根就被逮捕了  我不觉得是巧合
that Corrigan was arrested after our conversation.

449
00:24:19,530 --> 00:24:21,450
我也不觉得是巧合
Well, I wouldn't think it was a coincidence either.

450
00:24:21,450 --> 00:24:23,330
那你有什么期望
So what do you hope to achieve?

451
00:24:23,330 --> 00:24:25,450
我的期望和你一样  让科里根先生获释
The same thing as you do: Mr. Corrigan's release.

452
00:24:25,450 --> 00:24:27,180
前提是我撤回决议案
If I withdraw the resolution.

453
00:24:27,180 --> 00:24:30,030
我认为莫斯科肯定会将此举视为善意的表示
I think Moscow would certainly see it as a sign of goodwill.

454
00:24:30,520 --> 00:24:32,060
我们可不会为了表示善意
Well, we don't barter goodwill

455
00:24:32,060 --> 00:24:33,610
就拿美国公民的自由做交易
for the freedom of American citizens.

456
00:24:33,610 --> 00:24:36,800
我提议过将他立即驱逐出境
I actually advocated for his immediate deportation.

457
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:39,000
我也认为把他扔进大牢只能适得其反
I agree that tossing him in jail is counterproductive,

458
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,830
但高层心意已决
but my superiors are adamant.

459
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:43,440
帮佩特罗夫看清局势吧
Save Petrov from himself.

460
00:24:43,980 --> 00:24:45,730
我可没资格质疑他
It's not my place to question him.

461
00:24:45,730 --> 00:24:47,640
和你不同  我毕竟没嫁给总统
Unlike you, I'm not married to my boss.

462
00:24:50,930 --> 00:24:54,160
我会把克里姆林宫的立场转达给总统
I'll relay the Kremlin's position to the president.

463
00:24:57,890 --> 00:25:00,210
如果我们让步  约旦河谷计划就搁浅了
If we give in, the Jordan Valley plan is over

464
00:25:00,210 --> 00:25:02,990
还让俄罗斯人觉得他们可以漫天要价
and we show the Russians we can be blackmailed.

465
00:25:02,990 --> 00:25:05,280
难道我们眼睁睁让科里根坐穿牢底吗
So we're just supposed to let Corrigan rot away?

466
00:25:05,330 --> 00:25:07,630
我想如果我们在联合国保持强硬立场
I think if we continue to drive hard at the UN,

467
00:25:07,630 --> 00:25:08,870
我们就会有更多筹码
we'll gain leverage.

468
00:25:08,890 --> 00:25:10,160
凯茜怎么想
What does Cathy think?

469
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:10,830
她也同意
She agrees.

470
00:25:10,830 --> 00:25:14,000
只要科里根一天没放出来  我就得挨一天骂
I'm gonna take flak every day that Corrigan remains in jail.

471
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:15,740
如果你退步的话就会被骂死
And you'll take more if you back down.

472
00:25:15,740 --> 00:25:17,510
但这样一来我就得在新闻发布会上
But it does mean I have to get in front of the press

473
00:25:17,510 --> 00:25:19,700
两手空空地面对媒体
with absolutely nothing of substance to say.

474
00:25:19,710 --> 00:25:22,070
你在国会混了20年  没话找话你最拿手
You spent 20 years in Congress. You're good at that.

475
00:25:25,060 --> 00:25:26,340
听到你笑真好
It's good to hear you laugh.

476
00:25:27,580 --> 00:25:29,540
睡一会儿吧  我明天再打给你
Get some sleep. I'll call you tomorrow.

477
00:25:29,740 --> 00:25:30,480
晚安
Good night.

478
00:25:33,970 --> 00:25:36,850
具体是谁负责华盛顿和莫斯科之间的沟通
Who specifically is communicating between Washington and Moscow?

479
00:25:36,850 --> 00:25:38,960
两国之间的联络是由国务院
All of our communication is between the State Department

480
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:41,350
和俄罗斯外交部负责的  艾拉
and the Russian Foreign Ministry. Ayla.

481
00:25:41,470 --> 00:25:44,300
您在声明中一直称这是侵犯言论自由
In your statement, you persisted in calling this a free speech issue,

482
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:46,590
但同性恋权利难道不也是主题吗
but isn't gay rights really at the center of this?

483
00:25:46,880 --> 00:25:49,920
科里根先生是因为自由发表意见被捕的
Well, Mr. Corrigan was arrested for speaking his mind.

484
00:25:49,940 --> 00:25:50,710
无论他是持什么立场
No matter what his opinions...

485
00:25:50,710 --> 00:25:52,010
您是不是在回避问题  总统先生
Aren't you skirting that, Mr. President,

486
00:25:52,010 --> 00:25:54,160
因为您在同性恋权利问题上立场含混不清
because your stance on gay rights is unclear?

487
00:25:56,900 --> 00:26:00,060
现在清楚无疑的是科里根先生的被捕不公正
What is clear is that Mr. Corrigan's detainment is unjust

488
00:26:00,060 --> 00:26:02,190
而如我所言  我们正动用一切手段
and, as I said, we're doing everything we can

489
00:26:02,220 --> 00:26:03,980
确保他安全回家  扎克利
to make sure that he can come home. Yes, Zachary.

490
00:26:03,980 --> 00:26:04,740
我还没问完
Following up.

491
00:26:04,740 --> 00:26:06,310
如果您不参选  那么回避同性恋问题
Isn't dodging gay rights a calculated move

492
00:26:06,310 --> 00:26:08,140
是不是太过算计了
for a man not running for office?

493
00:26:09,690 --> 00:26:10,930
你说我在回避问题
You think I'm dodging?

494
00:26:11,710 --> 00:26:14,200
那我今天就把话跟你说清楚
Well, then let me be as clear as I possibly can be.

495
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,150
同性恋群体是有权利的
Gay people have rights.

496
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:18,190
而本届政府始终坚信
And this administration has always believed

497
00:26:18,190 --> 00:26:20,520
科里根先生有权就任何问题
that Mr. Corrigan has the right to speak his mind

498
00:26:20,690 --> 00:26:23,050
自由表达观点  而无需担心被捕
without fear of being arrested on any issue,

499
00:26:23,050 --> 00:26:25,250
不管是同性恋权利还是别的什么
whether it's gay rights or something else.

500
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:26,550
另一件清楚无疑的事
And what is also quite clear

501
00:26:26,550 --> 00:26:28,670
就是你在礼仪课上肯定没好好听讲
is that you must have failed etiquette class.

502
00:26:29,200 --> 00:26:29,920
扎克利
Yes, Zachary.

503
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:31,520
-总统先生  -您为什么不接见约翰·帕斯特纳克
- Mr. Prisident-- - Why won't you speak to John Pasternak,

504
00:26:31,520 --> 00:26:32,180
-迈克尔·科里根的丈夫  -萨伊德女士
- Michael Corrigan's husband? - Ms. Sayyad,

505
00:26:32,180 --> 00:26:33,920
今天到场的还有其他记者和媒体
there are other members of the press here today,

506
00:26:33,920 --> 00:26:35,570
帕斯特纳克先生一直在试图联系白宫
Mr. Pasternak has been trying to contact the White House

507
00:26:35,570 --> 00:26:36,760
但却没人理他
and no one will speak with him.

508
00:26:36,770 --> 00:26:38,080
实在抱歉各位  我还有会
I do apologize, I have a meeting.

509
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:39,720
真希望能回答你们所有人的问题
I wish I could've gotten to all your questions.

510
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:41,140
还有任何疑问的话
But if you have any further inquiries,

511
00:26:41,140 --> 00:26:43,270
请问格雷森先生  非常感谢
please direct them to Mr. Grayson. Thank you very much.

512
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:45,530
抱歉  先生
I apologize, sir.

513
00:26:48,540 --> 00:26:49,380
你太过分了
You went too far.

514
00:26:49,380 --> 00:26:50,480
那是我的工作
