00:35:41,170 --> 00:35:42,680
现在方便吗  邓巴女士
Is this a good time, Ms. Dunbar?

696
00:35:42,890 --> 00:35:43,870
你是哪位
Who is this?

697
00:35:44,380 --> 00:35:45,470
道格·斯坦普
Doug Stamper.

698
00:35:47,100 --> 00:35:48,390
你怎么拿到这个号码的
How did you get this number?

699
00:35:49,050 --> 00:35:51,550
拿到号码很简单  你应该问的是
Phone numbers are easy. What you should be asking

700
00:35:51,550 --> 00:35:54,130
我怎么知道你今晚要跟吉阿罗参议员见面
is how I knew you were meeting with Senator Giallo tonight.

701
00:35:55,720 --> 00:35:56,790
回头看走廊
Look down the hallway.

702
00:36:00,950 --> 00:36:02,380
你们先走  我到下面找你们
Go ahead. I'll meet you down there.

703
00:36:02,380 --> 00:36:03,180
好吧
All right.

704
00:36:05,620 --> 00:36:07,080
别过来  待在原地
No. Stay where you are.

705
00:36:07,560 --> 00:36:09,220
我们不能被别人看到在一起
We wouldn't want to be seen together.

706
00:36:11,270 --> 00:36:12,770
总统派你来的吗
Did the president send you?

707
00:36:13,850 --> 00:36:16,840
不是  我们不联系了
No. He and I aren't in touch.

708
00:36:17,610 --> 00:36:18,830
那你为什么来这里
Then why are you here?

709
00:36:19,020 --> 00:36:22,260
你要组竞选团队  我想加入
You're forming your team. I want to be a part of it.

710
00:36:22,260 --> 00:36:23,350
真实原因呢
The real reason.

711
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:25,120
这就是原因
That is the reason.

712
00:36:25,780 --> 00:36:28,160
他派你来的  别骗我
He sent you. Don't lie to me.

713
00:36:30,980 --> 00:36:33,360
我已经九个月没参与任何事了  邓巴女士
I've been out of the game for nine months, Ms. Dunbar.

714
00:36:33,850 --> 00:36:35,060
我想重回战局
I want to get back in.

715
00:36:35,780 --> 00:36:36,660
你要组建竞选团队
You're forming your team,

716
00:36:36,660 --> 00:36:38,320
我想成为开朝一员
and I want to get in on the ground floor.

717
00:36:40,590 --> 00:36:42,060
光有领导层还不够
The leadership isn't enough.

718
00:36:45,310 --> 00:36:46,700
你还需要基层人士
You need the rank and file.

719
00:36:47,330 --> 00:36:50,090
他们与各市县权力掮客的关系
Their connections to county and municipal power brokers.

720
00:36:50,830 --> 00:36:52,290
从初选开始到全面展开
The chiefs of a thousand kingdoms

721
00:36:52,290 --> 00:36:55,050
每一场选举中的当权人物
in every primary from Iowa to Super Tuesday.

722
00:36:56,020 --> 00:36:58,070
我在党鞭办公室工作了十年
I worked in the whip's office for ten years.

723
00:36:58,280 --> 00:37:00,360
我手上有每个人的资料
I have files on every single member.

724
00:37:00,950 --> 00:37:04,740
他们要什么  跟谁睡  中午吃什么
What they want, who they sleep with, what they eat for lunch.

725
00:37:05,150 --> 00:37:06,510
我对你会很有价值
I can be valuable to you.

726
00:37:07,230 --> 00:37:09,790
你怎么知道我今晚要跟吉阿罗见面
How did you know I was meeting with Giallo tonight?

727
00:37:10,220 --> 00:37:12,060
你跟领导层来往密切
You rub shoulders with the leadership.

728
00:37:12,170 --> 00:37:14,380
我跟为他们工作的人来往密切
I rub shoulders with the people who work for them.

729
00:37:20,780 --> 00:37:23,510
考虑一下吧  邓巴女士  我只有这点请求
Think about it, Ms. Dunbar. That's all I ask.

730
00:37:23,510 --> 00:37:24,560
下楼
Going down.

731
00:37:30,900 --> 00:37:32,300
我犯了个错误
I made a mistake.

732
00:37:32,950 --> 00:37:35,550
她在总统办公室里跟我说话的方式
I mean, the way she spoke to me in the Oval,

733
00:37:35,550 --> 00:37:37,170
让我恨不得勒死她
I wanted to strangle her.

734
00:37:38,430 --> 00:37:39,990
她到底在想什么
I mean, what is she thinking?

735
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:41,900
跟在职总统竞争
Running against an incumbent

736
00:37:41,900 --> 00:37:44,250
我都提出给她最高法的职位了
when I offered her a seat on the court--

737
00:37:44,260 --> 00:37:46,790
博奇向她吹耳边风时  她就决定要参选了
She was going to run the moment Birch whispered in her ear.

738
00:37:47,020 --> 00:37:48,800
人一旦开始想象自己坐在总统办公室里
Once people imagine themselves in the Oval,

739
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:49,850
就不会再回头了
there's no turning back.

740
00:37:49,850 --> 00:37:51,480
你跟他们一样清楚
You know that as well as anybody.

741
00:37:51,570 --> 00:37:54,950
是我自己的错  不应该给雅各布斯留选择余地
It's my own damn fault. Shouldn't have given Jacobs the choice.

742
00:37:54,950 --> 00:37:57,540
我应该在问她之前就宣布提名
I should've just announced her nomination before I even asked her.

743
00:37:57,540 --> 00:37:59,130
-需要我回家吗  -不用
- Should I come home? - No.

744
00:38:00,720 --> 00:38:03,300
我只需要考虑一下  理清思路
I just need to think. I need to clear my head.

745
00:38:04,090 --> 00:38:05,310
我能做点什么
Tell me what I can do.

746
00:38:08,990 --> 00:38:10,670
我为什么要有所保留
Why did I hold back?

747
00:38:11,720 --> 00:38:14,110
我为什么要对雅各布斯留情
Why did I show Jacobs any mercy?

748
00:38:14,110 --> 00:38:16,380
弗兰西斯  这可不像你的作风
Francis, this doesn't sound like you.

749
00:38:17,290 --> 00:38:19,830
把这些抛在脑后  想想下一步怎么做
Put this behind you. Think about what's next.

750
00:38:22,250 --> 00:38:24,080
是因为默罕默德
It was because of Mahmoud.

751
00:38:25,970 --> 00:38:27,520
我让他影响了我
I let him get to me.

752
00:38:29,850 --> 00:38:33,530
那些士兵灵柩上的国旗
And all those flags on those coffins and those soldiers, whose--

753
00:38:34,290 --> 00:38:37,100
我调派  又下葬了他们  是我的...
I deployed and then I buried in the ground. It's my--

754
00:38:37,100 --> 00:38:39,990
别说了  这帮不上忙
Stop it. This isn't doing you any good.

755
00:38:39,990 --> 00:38:42,270
你想谈的话我可以跟你谈
I will talk about this with you if you want,

756
00:38:42,530 --> 00:38:44,590
但我不允许你怀疑自己
but if you're doubting yourself, I can't indulge that.

757
00:38:44,590 --> 00:38:46,100
是啊  你说得对
No, you're right, of course.

758
00:38:47,430 --> 00:38:48,740
明早再谈吧
Well, let's talk in the morning.

759
00:38:48,740 --> 00:38:50,670
-有需要随时找我  -我知道
- I'm here if you need me. - I know.

760
00:38:52,820 --> 00:38:55,540
-晚安  -晚安  弗兰西斯
- Good night. - Good night, Francis.

761
00:39:19,910 --> 00:39:22,960
能帮我接艾迪斯主教吗
Yes, can you reach out to Bishop Eddis for me?

762
00:39:23,710 --> 00:39:24,590
我等着
I'll hold.

763
00:39:45,830 --> 00:39:46,910
谢谢  密查姆
Thank you, Meechum.

764
00:39:47,260 --> 00:39:49,590
-让我们单独谈谈  -好的
- If we can have some privacy. - Yes, sir.

765
00:39:52,020 --> 00:39:53,640
还骑博纳维尔呢
Still riding the Bonneville?

766
00:39:54,440 --> 00:39:57,740
把67款卖了换了派普伯恩  那车不错
Sold the '67 for a Pipeburn. Beautiful bike.

767
00:39:57,740 --> 00:39:59,840
有机会带我兜一圈
You should take me for a spin sometime.

768
00:40:00,380 --> 00:40:01,410
算了吧
I don't think so.

769
00:40:01,920 --> 00:40:03,200
骑那个太找死
They're a death wish.

770
00:40:03,980 --> 00:40:06,200
至少你知道自己能上天堂
At least you know you have a place in heaven.

771
00:40:10,980 --> 00:40:12,500
有什么事  总统先生
What's on your mind, Mr. President?

772
00:40:13,450 --> 00:40:14,960
那天葬礼
The burial the other day.

773
00:40:15,740 --> 00:40:17,740
你谈到了亚伯拉罕和以撒
You talked about Abraham and Isaac.

774
00:40:17,740 --> 00:40:20,490
上帝献出了他唯一的儿子
God giving up his only Son.

775
00:40:21,080 --> 00:40:21,870
就跟你说说
Between you and me,

776
00:40:21,870 --> 00:40:24,280
我在阿灵顿总说那一套
that's the same sermon I always use at Arlington.

777
00:40:25,110 --> 00:40:26,480
安葬的士兵太多
You put enough soldiers in the ground,

778
00:40:26,480 --> 00:40:28,180
就懒得写新悼词了
you get tired of writing new ones.

779
00:40:30,250 --> 00:40:32,070
那是我第一次听
It was the first time I had heard it.

780
00:40:32,210 --> 00:40:33,440
肯定不是最后一次
Won't be the last.

781
00:40:35,390 --> 00:40:37,830
我想理解正义
I want to understand what justice is.

782
00:40:39,800 --> 00:40:40,840
这可不简单
That's a big one.

783
00:40:41,420 --> 00:40:42,360
我知道
I know.

784
00:40:44,820 --> 00:40:47,500
我们的正义是先辈创造的
There's our justice, the kind men create.

785
00:40:48,740 --> 00:40:51,580
以《十诫》之类的戒律为基础
We base it on things like the Ten Commandments.

786
00:40:52,760 --> 00:40:54,870
但文字总有不同的解读方法
But those can be read a million different ways.

787
00:40:56,210 --> 00:40:58,550
"不可杀人"说的倒是很明确
"Thou shalt not kill" seems pretty clear.

788
00:40:59,330 --> 00:41:02,140
说得轻巧  我们不杀人
Who's to say? If we didn't kill,

789
00:41:02,930 --> 00:41:04,850
也许还有别人开杀戒
others would kill instead of us.

790
00:41:05,820 --> 00:41:07,510
《圣经》里谈了许多杀戮的故事
There's a lot of killing in the Bible.

791
00:41:08,330 --> 00:41:09,960
大卫王就是位勇士
King David was a warrior.

792
00:41:10,110 --> 00:41:13,870
那怎么用上帝给摩西的《十诫》解释他的行为呢
How do you reconcile that with the laws that God gave Moses?

793
00:41:14,750 --> 00:41:16,990
《十诫》也可以有不同解读
Even those laws require interpretation.

794
00:41:18,700 --> 00:41:21,590
有两条一定要记牢
There are two laws we have to remember above all else.

795
00:41:23,860 --> 00:41:27,040
他要我们爱上帝
He tells us to love God

796
00:41:27,440 --> 00:41:28,660
还要互敬互爱
and to love each other.

797
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:33,130
怎么去爱你杀的人
You can't love the people you kill.

798
00:41:34,390 --> 00:41:35,740
当然可以
You sure as hell can.

799
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:38,780
想杀你的人  你也要去爱
And you have to love the people who are trying to kill you.

800
00:41:40,640 --> 00:41:42,040
耶稣也爱罗马人
Jesus loved the Romans.

801
00:41:42,820 --> 00:41:44,040
他说  "天父  原谅他们吧
"Father, forgive them," He said,

802
00:41:44,050 --> 00:41:45,650
他们并不清楚自己的所作所为"
"For they know not what they do."

803
00:41:47,230 --> 00:41:48,530
他为什么不反抗
Why didn't he fight?

804
00:41:49,140 --> 00:41:51,880
他为什么自愿牺牲
Why did he allow himself to be sacrificed?

805
00:41:53,320 --> 00:41:55,520
我自问过许多遍
I ask myself that question a lot.

806
00:41:55,690 --> 00:41:58,140
我理解《旧约》的上帝
I understand the Old Testament God,

807
00:41:58,140 --> 00:41:59,600
权力至高无上
whose power is absolute,

808
00:41:59,600 --> 00:42:02,970
用恐惧统治人类  但是他...
who rules through fear, but... him.

809
00:42:09,750 --> 00:42:12,620
人类无法拥有至高无上的权力
There's no such thing as absolute power for us,

810
00:42:12,740 --> 00:42:14,690
只能接受上帝的统治
except on the receiving end.

811
00:42:15,580 --> 00:42:17,550
用恐惧统治不会有好下场
Using fear will get you nowhere.

812
00:42:17,710 --> 00:42:20,250
你的工作不是裁决正义
It's not your job to determine what's just.

813
00:42:20,680 --> 00:42:24,260
你也无权决定喜欢哪个上帝
It's not your place to choose the version of God you like best.

814
00:42:24,330 --> 00:42:26,220
你不必一个人效忠国家
It's not your duty to serve this country alone,

815
00:42:26,220 --> 00:42:29,220
也最好不要只想着为自己牟利
and it better not be your goal to simply serve yourself.

816
00:42:30,060 --> 00:42:31,260
你效忠主
You serve the Lord.

817
00:42:31,920 --> 00:42:33,870
通过他效忠众生
And through Him, you serve others.

818
00:42:35,310 --> 00:42:36,400
两条规则
Two rules.

819
00:42:36,950 --> 00:42:39,420
爱上帝  互敬互爱
Love God. Love each other.

820
00:42:40,190 --> 00:42:41,120
就这样
Period.

821
00:42:42,580 --> 00:42:44,390
你不是救世主  总统先生
You weren't chosen, Mr. President.

822
00:42:47,800 --> 00:42:48,920
他才是
Only he was.

823
00:42:56,080 --> 00:42:57,750
我能单独待一会儿吗
May I have a few moments?

824
00:42:58,060 --> 00:43:01,000
一个人待着  祈祷
For myself. To pray.

825
00:43:03,860 --> 00:43:04,880
可以啊
It's all yours.

826
00:43:38,400 --> 00:43:39,340
爱
Love?

827
00:43:40,600 --> 00:43:41,960
你就想推销这个吗
That's what you're selling?

828
00:43:46,320 --> 00:43:47,960
我不要
Well, I don't buy it.

829
00:44:12,810 --> 00:44:14,050
没事吧  先生
Is everything all right, sir?

830
00:44:15,950 --> 00:44:18,480
我在祈祷  他突然倒了
I was praying and it just fell.

831
00:44:43,580 --> 00:44:45,360
找个人清理一下
Please have someone clean this up.

832
00:44:46,240 --> 00:44:47,260
好的  先生
Yes, sir.

833
00:44:48,370 --> 00:44:49,970
这下我有上帝的耳朵了[上帝肯听我的了]
Well, I've got God's ear now.

